  "storyboard_markdown": "# Scene Contract: CH005_SC003\n\n## Production Intent\nResolve the physical immobilization of the Tin Woodman through lubrication, transitioning the group dynamic from a rescue mission to an expanded traveling party.\n\n## Required Cast\n- dorothy (young human girl, weary traveler, white dress)\n- the_scarecrow (companion)\n- tin_woodman (metal/tin character, initially rusted/immobile)\n\n## Required Environments\n- forest_and_cottage_setting (specifically cottage_interior)\n\n## Continuity Constraints\n- The \"wetness\" or sheen of the oil on the tin surfaces must be consistent during application and movement.\n- Mechanical movement must transition from jerking/staccato to fluid as lubrication progresses.\n\n## Beat List\n- BT001: Discovery of the oil-can in the cottage.\n- BT002: Application of oil to the Tin Woodman's joints and restoration of movement.\n- BT003: The Tin Woodman awakens and declares his quest for a heart.",
